This paper deals with off-policy evaluation in Markov decision processes, which is a problem commonly studied in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of importance sampling is a popular technique in this area, which suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the estimation of a behavior policy, which is a statistical problem, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper deals with Markov decision processes, which are commonly studied in the field of robotics, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics).
